<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued September 08 at 6:59AM CDT until September 08 at 7:15AM CDT by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 715 AM CDT
FOR SOUTHEASTERN SCOTT AND NORTHEASTERN POLK COUNTIES...
At 659 AM CDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from near Cardiff to 8 miles south of Waldron, moving
southeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Cardiff...                        Y City...
Nola...                           Needmore...
Olio...                           Cedar Creek...
Cherry Hill in Polk County...     Harvey...
Boles...                          Parks...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
